This is a historic pistol in being John Moses Brownings first Semi Automatic design in his prolific firearms designing/inventing career. This gun is known as the grandfather of the 1911 and the one that started it all. This gun was manufactured in 1907 and is in fantastic shape for being 105 years old and retains about 70% of its original lustourus charcoal blue finish. title: For Sale/Trade:  .22 sniper rifle
postcontent:
This project started with what was one of the most accurate .22 rifle out of the box and then turned into I wonder if a .22 can be a sniper rifle. I know, ridiculous... but the most fun I have had with a gun by far.

It was born as a shiny innocent Marlin 60W with a 22" micro groove barrel. As I watched it get older, it's body started going through changes and grew into an ATI fiberforce dragunov stock. 
Next, it got taller, as all little ones do, by standing on a precision-grade bipod with spring-loaded folding legs made from durable aircraft-grade aluminum and steel and towering 11". 
Ahh how they grow up.
 However, as it went through it's awkwardness, I quickly came to realize that it needed glasses. We fought back and forth over this as it did not want anything awkward as to avoid being made fun of by other rifles. Finally, we compromised with the sexy sleek design of a BSA 6-24x Mildot scope that is waterproof, shock proof, and fog proof. Of course it wanted the 4" sunshade and who am I to say no to such an adorable little rifle. 

Now that it is all grown up, it needs to venture out into the world and make it's own mark. I know it will make the best decisions possible in it's journey as it is a very dependable, reliable, and accurate little whipper snapper.
